body.name: Thermalright TL-C12C X3 CPU Fan 120mm Case Cooler Fan, 4pin PWM Silent Computer Fan with S-FDB Bearing Included, up to 1550RPM Cooling Fan（3 Quantities）
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Monday, February 19 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
features: 【High Performance Cooling Fan】 Automatic speed control of the motherboard through the 4PIN PWM fan cable interface, which can determine the speed according to the temperature of the motherboard, with a maximum speed of 1550RPM. Configured with up to 55cm of cable for PWM series control of fans, ideal for cases and CPU coolers.

【Quality Bearings】The carefully developed quality S-FDB bearings solve the problem of pc cooling fan blade shaking in lifting mode, keeping fan noise to a minimum while providing maximum cooling performance when needed and extending the life of the fan.

【Vibration reduction and low noise】 The case fan is equipped with four soft material silicone corner pads on all four sides, which can reduce the vibration and friction caused by the rotation of the fan, perfectly reducing noise and allowing low noise operation, so that cooling can be carried out in low noise.

【Silent Fan Size】 Model: TL-C12C X3, Size: 120*120*25mm, Speed: 1550RPM±10%, Noise ≤ 25.6dBA Connector: 4pin pwm, Current: 0.20A, Air Pressure: 1.53mm H2O, Air Flow: 66.17CFM, Higher air flow for improved cooling performance.

【Perfect Match】The PC fan can be used not only as a case fan, but is also suitable for use with a cpu cooler to create a cooling effect together, which can take away the dry heat from the case and the high temperature generated by the CPU in operation, allowing for maximum cooling; Ideal for cases, radiators and CPU coolers.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: LONG LASTING S-FDB BEARING Fan Motor equipped with high durability S-FDB (Fluid Dynamic Bearing) bearing, proving low-friction and low-noise operation. For a long service life span in your PC build. Thermalright fan with S-FDB bearing is maintenance-free, please do not disassemble. POWER FROM DESIGN After years of engineering, Thermalright comes up the original design of TL-C12C, able to maximize airflow within 1550RPM fan speed. Focus on balance between airflow and static pressure performance, the Thermalright TL-C12C fan series is a all-around choice for heatsink, radiator or computer case cooling scenarios. BUILD TOUGH, THINK ERGONOMIC Fan blades and frames are made of industrial grade PBT composite PC polymer to ensure stability in computer use. Each corner of the fan is pre fitted with silicone rubber pads for noise and vibration damping

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredibly cheap, stable and quiet fans. But man these screws hurt!
reviews.reviewText: Loved these fans. I needed some cheap options for my case so I can drop the temps down during Cyberpunk Liberty.The noise change is miniscule compared to my single start fan in the front and my microphone is close by, can't even tell the difference.I googled a video of how to install these just to be safe and theres a grear video on youtube. There are 4 cords to each fan, 2 are for daisy chaining the power and the other two daisy chaining the color sync.The screws are horrendously bad to get in.At least 2 out of the 4 on each fan were so hard to turn in it feels like you have to make new thread in the fans. I had four screws from an old corsair fan to put in each of them to save my hands a little work, but I'm talking my hand got close to a few blisters from turning the screws in. So just be prepared that you may have to work hard to screw in these fans.But overall they are gorgeous, extremely cheap and feel durable. I'm excited to have them and would give these an easy 5 star.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Impressive value for money
reviews.reviewText: I got these for a recent budget build and was super surprised by how decent these are for the price. They're certainly nothing spectacular from a performance perspective, but they're mad cheap and spin well enough. The RGB works totally fine, no issues out of the box with an MSI motherboard. They stay pretty quiet as well, placed in the front of a Corsair D4000 airflow you really don't hear them most of the time. The cables are daisy chain-able, so while cabeling can get messy quick, you likely don't have to worry about running out of mobo headers. Overall I think if you're just trying to keep cost down as much as possible, you can't really go wrong with these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Built from decent materials and they’re PWM. Also pretty cheap. They’re mostly quiet as well, but not silent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bang for the buck ARGB PWM fans!
reviews.reviewText: These things are actually amazing for the price at just around $13 for a 3 pack of White, ARGB, PWM fans that have a decently high maximum RPM, and are fairly quiet!They have a daisy chain system, so you only need to plug in 1 3 pin ARGB header and 1 4 pin fan header, and the others can daisy chain to keep cable management out of site!Can control the RGB colors via software which is also very convenient.Overall, these are the only way to go if you want ARGB PWM fans for a very affordable price!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good inexpensive fan
reviews.reviewText: Great for case flow, rgb works good and can daisy chain rgb and pwm fans together.Con: box 2 (3 fan set) only provided enough screws for 1 fan. Other box had enough screws for all 3 fans. Also fan screws are small and pop through the case lining.

reviews.reviewText: If you get enough fans they all tend to stay quieter since they don't have to work as hard -- and it's easy to get a lot of fans when they're $5 each. This is the best fan deal I've seen. They work and they look fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It is cheap, it is Thermalright and it works great!
reviews.reviewText: First of all, you can't find a better deal on RGB fans, period. Unless they raise the price in the future. Since the price is so dam cheap, I just placed another 2 orders for the white ones for my future builds...Back to the topic, it is pretty loud at max rpm but totally acceptable at about 650 rpm, which is very ideal for case fans. RGB is smooth, fans are daisy chained, it even has laser authentic stickers on the fans.You simply just cant find anything better at this price point.
fans work, rgb works, dirt cheap. no complaints. would have been nice with white screws instead of silver but whatever

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Look great but one fan came broken
reviews.reviewText: Look great and do the job but one fan was damaged in transit but could probably issue a refund and resolve the problem. Otherwise great fans for the price.

The fans are a great buy. I used these for my first PC build and chose them based off a lot of reviews on the product on different platforms. I bought 2 x3 packs and am currently using 4 fans for my Ryzen 7 5700G APU. Idle temps with low usage (YouTube, some browser tabs open) are around 28C - 32C with heavy load temps around 55C - 64C with just the 4 fans + AMD stock CPU Cooler (obviously depends on where people live as temps will vary with environment). When under load the noise level is still relatively low with the obvious air woosh increase. Best I can describe is when under load and my door is closed, you're not hearing anything outside. And if wearing headphones you're barely hearing anything.The only issue that was a bit frustrating was screwing them in as some of the screws would just be very hard to screw in.Overall for the price, quality and performance I highly recommend these fans.
